root ignore
Type: object

ignore patterns to skip interface, ip address or routing objects

root ignore ipaddr
Type: array of string

list of ip address prefixes to be ignored

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root ignore ipaddr ipaddr items
Type: string

ip address with prefix length
Example:

fe80::/10

root ignore ifname
Type: array of string

interface names matching this list of regex will be ignored

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root ignore ifname ifname items
Type: string

regex to match interface name
Examples:

^docker\d+

^lo$

^ppp\d+$

^veth

root ignore routes
Type: object

filter routes by options

root ignore routes protos
Type: array of integer
No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root ignore routes protos protos items
Type: integer

protocol number (/etc/iproute2/rt_protos)

root interfaces
Type: array of object

list of interface settings (link settings and ip addresses)

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root interfaces interfaces items
Type: object

root interfaces interfaces items name
Type: string

name of the interface

root interfaces interfaces items addresses
Type: array of string

ip addresses of the interface

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root interfaces interfaces items addresses addresses items
Type: string

Examples:

192.0.2.1

192.168.0.1/24

2001:db8::1/64

root interfaces interfaces items link

link settings of the interface

  • Option 1
  • Option 2
  • Option 3
  • Option 4
  • Option 5
  • Option 6
  • Option 7
  • Option 8
  • Option 9
root interfaces interfaces items link oneOf item 0
Type: object

generic interface

root interfaces interfaces items link oneOf item 0 kind
Type: enum (of string)

link type

Must be one of:

  • "bond"
  • "bridge"
  • "gtp"
  • "ip6tnl"
  • "ipoib"
  • "ipvlan"
  • "macvlan"
  • "macvtap"
  • "physical"
  • "team"
  • "tuntap"
  • "veth"
  • "vrf"
  • "vti"
  • "vti6"

root interfaces interfaces items link oneOf item 0 master
Type: integer or string

specifies a master device name or index

root interfaces interfaces items link oneOf item 0 state
Type: enum (of string)

set device state

Must be one of:

  • "up"
  • "down"
